♪ Say it like you mean it ♪

01:35.938 --> 01:38.822
♪ Bones becomes dust ♪

01:39.692 --> 01:42.209
♪ Gold turns to rust ♪

01:43.429 --> 01:46.096
♪ Say it like you mean it ♪

01:48.100 --> 01:49.900
♪ Mmmm ♪

01:50.636 --> 01:53.537
♪ Underneath a spotlight ♪

01:57.309 --> 02:00.411
♪ And all the splintered wood ♪

02:00.446 --> 02:03.030
- It's okay, I'll wait.
- ♪ Nothing here is shining ♪

02:03.065 --> 02:04.982
I'm only the King of England.

02:05.017 --> 02:07.618
♪ Shining like it should ♪

02:09.255 --> 02:11.388
♪ Mmmm ♪

02:13.125 --> 02:16.126
- ♪ I'd rather watch my kingdom fall ♪
- Your Majesty?

02:16.162 --> 02:18.328
Walk away. I'll do it myself.

02:19.432 --> 02:23.567
♪ I want it all or not at all ♪

02:32.878 --> 02:36.013
A breakfast fit for a king.

02:36.048 --> 02:38.081
What is it?

02:38.134 --> 02:40.951
- For me?
- Don't get over-excited.

02:40.986 --> 02:43.353
It's a going away present.
You're being dismissed.

02:43.389 --> 02:46.790
- Did I do something wrong?
- Your job. Too well.

02:46.826 --> 02:48.325
Enter!

02:52.882 --> 02:55.232
Congratulations. You're rehired.

02:55.284 --> 02:58.735
From now on, you'll be known
as Lady of the Privy Chamber.

02:59.472 --> 03:03.073
I want you to be devoted to
my well-being full-time.

03:03.442 --> 03:05.576
And since you'll no longer
be wearing a uniform,

03:05.611 --> 03:07.961
I thought a new wardrobe was in order.

03:10.983 --> 03:12.816
You really didn't need
to do any of this.

03:12.852 --> 03:14.835
I just like taking care of you.

03:15.504 --> 03:17.454
I wanted to.

03:17.490 --> 03:19.156
Go on. Open them.

03:20.960 --> 03:24.027
(Door opens and closes)

03:25.698 --> 03:28.916
Your Majesty, I am very sorry,

03:28.968 --> 03:31.702
but I was unable to deliver it.

03:32.204 --> 03:34.204
Captain Lacey's house was deserted.

03:34.240 --> 03:37.624
His car is gone and his neighbors said

03:37.676 --> 03:39.576
there's been no sign of him for months.

03:39.612 --> 03:41.245
And his mobile?

03:42.014 --> 03:43.680
Disconnected. I am sorry.

03:44.950 --> 03:47.851
You did tell him not to contact you

03:47.887 --> 03:50.020
following the paternity scandal.

03:50.055 --> 03:52.856
Perhaps he's just doing
as he was instructed.

03:53.475 --> 03:55.125
Perhaps?

03:56.662 --> 03:59.263
When I went to see Captain Lacey,

03:59.298 --> 04:01.031
after your television interview,

04:01.066 --> 04:03.500
he was angry with you, Ma'am.

04:03.536 --> 04:06.019
For using Henry's identity
to conceal the truth.

04:08.090 --> 04:09.740
Why didn't you tell me that before?

04:09.775 --> 04:11.475
The King had just been stabbed.

04:11.510 --> 04:14.177
You were in the midst
of a paternity scandal.

04:14.647 --> 04:16.747
I really didn't want to burden you.

04:19.485 --> 04:21.918
Very well. Thank you, Lucius.

04:21.954 --> 04:23.620
Your Majesty.

04:26.592 --> 04:28.575
(Door opens then closes)

